## Early game

**Hellas** on Mars (Exterminate, Grineer Settlement, levels 8-10) is a quick
way to stock up early: Mars is one of Gallium's two signature planets, and a
short Exterminate is easy to repeat for a fresh account. **Gradivus**
(Sabotage) on the same planet is a good secondary stop — its resource cache
carries a decent Gallium chance too.

## Mid & late game

**Titania** on Uranus (Assassination, Tyl Regor, Steel Path) is the strongest
endgame option: Tyl Regor has his own Gallium drop on top of Uranus being
Gallium's other signature planet, so repeat boss kills with a Steel Path
squad scale well per hour. Because Gallium mostly comes from mission
completion and resource caches rather than regular enemy kills, a Resource
Drop Booster is worth stacking on top for the cache-based portion of the run.

